&lt;P&gt;&lt;BR&gt;We never had full.&amp;nbsp; Not even close.&amp;nbsp; It would be closer to 30 mins before we got to full.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;What we did have is when we got rezzed, we would still have the endurance we had prior to rez.&amp;nbsp; Which was just enough to pop Fortitude/Defensive after AET with maybe a bit for bellow.&amp;nbsp; It still required the raid to pay attention to not snake aggro from the warrior.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Personally, I have no issues with them making endurance work just like mana and having it zapped when rezzed.&amp;nbsp; But if they are going to make endurance behave like mana for rezzes, they should make it behave like mana for EVERYTHING ELSE!&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;That means emergency mana recovery mechanism like mod rods and paragon should also provide for emergency endurance recovery.&amp;nbsp; Similarly, divine rez which gives you 100% mana, should ALSO give you 100% endurance.&amp;nbsp; Right now, even GM rez does not restore endurance.&amp;nbsp; I don't even mind the lack of long term endurance regen buffs.&amp;nbsp; But it's the double whammy of endurance behaving like mana *AND* the fact that there's zero way to even attempt an emergency endurance recovery that really makes this situation annoying.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;It effectively neuters the warriors when they get rezzed into a combat situation.&lt;/P&gt;</description>
