&lt;P&gt;I'll give you a picture tho of what a Paladin does when he gets rezzed. Ok first thing you loot up fast and sit down to start medding. Then you load up BSG/Armor of Unrelenting Faith and Pious Fury (well I do, it's a cheap buff and helps fill up them early buff slots). I chuck in a couple clickies then do pious, BSG, then armor (of those 3 buffs, if i get dots piled on me and stuff starts overwriting from the front, that's the order i'd wanna lose em in). After this I med again and sort out my spell in line up. At this point I've got like 1 to 1.5 left on my rez timer. From this point you should have a couple nice mana buffs, and hopefully your mana regen AA/gear isn't too shabby. When you first stand up, forget healing, we're not rdy for that yet. Ideally you're gonna stick to dps for a bit, you can tank, if you're lucky you might have just enough&amp;nbsp;endurance for that rune disc - maybe not tho, you can fire some stuns and hold aggro.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;In this situation if we want to get mana for heals, if we *have to aggro* we have to do it as leanly as possible.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
