      <title>Re: Weekly Question:  Week of October 9th</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&amp;message.id=26058#M26058</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;You are right in the respect that there is a discrepancy in the fact that some casters have means of regaining mana post rez in combat.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;What I disagree with from my perspective as a Paladin is that necro's will never pump a freshly rezzed paladin, the chances of me in mid combat getting clarity are next to nill as are the chances that I will catch a paragon because I might need it while others may not.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;The theory that any one should come in with a rez with endurance returned is what I dispute.&amp;nbsp; Just as much as outside of Divine Rez, people shouldn't come back with mana in their pool either.&amp;nbsp; They are the same thing, one is yellow, one is blue.&amp;nbsp; Fight the fact that they are the same all you want, but they are.&amp;nbsp; Yes, Endurance needs to have added to it the bonus effects that come with mana as well, but coming into a fight, ready to go with atleast one disc.. that I disagree with.&amp;nbsp; That's like me coming alive with the ability to group heal, or have full well ready every form of agro I have... neither of which is the case.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Ironically, hybrids take a double hit in this due to using both endurance and mana.&amp;nbsp; Granted though, a second wind type of gathering endurance would actually be pretty cool to see.&lt;/P&gt;</description>
