&lt;P&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Lots of things here.&amp;nbsp; first, you being too cheap to buy clarity potions means you got no place complaining you can't get clarity when rezzed in.&amp;nbsp; You could have it easily.&amp;nbsp; This is just one of a number of possible mana regen buffs you can get in this situation, and if your group/raid values your casting, then they will see to it you get at least some of them.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Believe it or not, if I am just rezzed in on a raid fight where the mob has anything approaching decent DPS, if I don't take the time to get buffs, I am not going to last more than a few seconds either.&amp;nbsp; That is just how things are.&amp;nbsp; This has zero to do with anything.&amp;nbsp; If your raid is in a situation of sending in people immedietly after rez to try and tank, without buffs, the raid is already in alot of trouble.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Now, lets look at a more realistic situation.&amp;nbsp; You get rezzed in mid raid.&amp;nbsp; You click your C potion.&amp;nbsp; You are now at 14 + 20(FT) =34(actually, with AA's and base standing regen, higher) mana per tick, while meleeing.&amp;nbsp; You are already gaining mana back faster than I am gaining endurence back.&amp;nbsp; If your enchanters are paying attention, you will actually get Intuition, for 44 mana regen just from that and FT.&amp;nbsp; If you raid happens to have a bard AEing mana, you are doing much better.&amp;nbsp; Add in mod rod, and SE(11 per tick), and your mana regen is not going to be bad at all, and these should be available to you post rez if it is a crisis situation, as getting healers and tanks back and effective is usually key when things aregoing wrong.&amp;nbsp; If things are not going wrong, it does not matter much anyway, as you can click your haste potion and be doing at least some DPS while those who have not died finish things off, then med.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Lastly, and importantly, this is not an us vs them situation.&amp;nbsp; If the issue is addressed, and returned to the way things where pre-TSS, &lt;STRONG&gt;it will have no negative impact on knights&lt;/STRONG&gt;, none.&amp;nbsp; It won't make warriors more competitive for group/raid spots, it won't affect relative class balance, it will just remove a negative thing that warriors(and other melee) have to deal with currently.&amp;nbsp; I am surprised that you did not complain about the last weekly question, dealing with strikethrough spam, as it affects knights just as much as this one.&lt;/P&gt;</description>
